The paper discusses a new algorithm for solving least-mean squares problems, which is a fundamental machine learning problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The algorithm also involves data summarization techniques, which suggests that it could be relevant to categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also mentions an example application in computer vision (boosting the performance of LMS solvers), which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well. Finally, the paper claims that the algorithm can be generalized for streaming and distributed data, which suggests that it could be relevant to categories such as cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) that deal with large-scale numerical computations.
